LightGCN (He et al., 2020) is a light graph neural network (GNN) model
for recommendation, in which only the item and user embedding need to be
learned, whereas non-linear operations are not considered. The basic concept
of LightGCN is to learn the user or item representation by aggregating the
information from multi-order neighbors in the user-item interaction graph.
