ranking scores where swaps only occur in settings where there
exists a reasonable chance of the documents being equally relevant,
quantified by the model’s uncertainty, 𝜎𝑞,𝑖.
In other words, we allow PUFR to pick ranking scores that max-
imize fairness in intervals [𝜇𝑞,𝑖−𝛼· 𝜎𝑞,𝑖, 𝜇𝑞,𝑖+ 𝛼· 𝜎𝑞,𝑖], without
re-ordering the documents within the same group. Here, 𝛼is a
user defined hyper-parameter that quantifies the chance of a utility
violation when performing this procedure. A higher value of 𝛼will
result in a fairer ranking but at the cost of less accurate predicted
scores, and hence potentially a drop in utility.
